    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onions are softening, add the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a tray with the <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give it a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the tomatoes are softened and starting to burst – these are your <strong>spiced roasted tomatoes</strong></p>",
